cdx6500NetServCfgTable.name: cdx6500NetServCfgTable
cdx6500NetServCfgTable.description: This table contains all the configuration objects for the Network Service Features.

cdx6500NetServCfgTableEntry.name: cdx6500NetServCfgTableEntry
cdx6500NetServCfgTableEntry.description: Parameters in the Network Services Configuration Table.

cdx6500NetServCfgEntryNumber.name: cdx6500NetServCfgEntryNumber
cdx6500NetServCfgEntryNumber.description: This is not a configurable parameter. This identifies the Network Services Configuration Table entry being configured by the other parameters in the record.

cdx6500NetServCfgPortAndStnId.name: cdx6500NetServCfgPortAndStnId
cdx6500NetServCfgPortAndStnId.description: This parameter identifies the port and station that the Network Services Data Compression feature will be enabled on. The wild card (match anything) character is * and can also be part of the entry. The following are the only valid port types: X25- (Examples: X25-1(16) or X25-1*) FRA- (Examples: FRA-3S1 or FRA-3*) LCON- (Examples: LCON-1 or LCON-*) TCOP- (Examples: TCOP-1 or TCOP-*) TBOP- (Examples: TBOP-1 or TBOP-*). NOTE: The hyphen is required and there should be no leading spaces. The range is 0-31 alphanumeric characters, the default value is blank.

cdx6500NetServCfgFeaturesLevel.name: cdx6500NetServCfgFeaturesLevel
cdx6500NetServCfgFeaturesLevel.description: This parameter specifies the Network Services features level. disable - The feature is not requested. negotiate - Negotiate for the feature. The feature is desired, but if not available bring up the virtual circuit anyway, without the feature. required - Required for call. Bring up the connection only if the feature is available on both ends. forceOn - The feature is required for the circuit to come up.
